      "writtenOn": "2026-06-04T02:23:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right now, The VPD changed the location code format `Ufcs-SCn/NDn-FRUn`, which broke the existing PEL code.\n\nThere was a discussion about how we want to represent the location code in the PIM. The rack label does not include a chassis number indication because it is part of the `Ufcs`, so having different location code formats could be confusing for customers and PEs.\n\nAs a result, the VPD team plans to revert to the original format and expects the chassis number information to be provided through the node number parameter. However, that change will take some time. In the meantime, we are adding a workaround in the PEL code to address the issue and will remove it once the VPD format is reverted.",
