    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "53fe08de_ee0268bc",
        "filename": "extensions/openpower-pels/src.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 1287,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000427
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-04T02:23:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think `run/openbmc/bmc_position` should be available for all system types (redundant-BMC multi-chassis, single-BMC multi-chassis, and single-BMC single-chassis) to provide a consistent interface.\n\nFor backward compatibility and lower-end systems, if `run/openbmc/bmc_position` is not present, we can assume chassis 0.\n\nSince chassis position is required for multi-chassis systems regardless of whether redundant BMC is enabled, I don\u0027t think this logic should depend solely on the redundant-BMC configuration option.",
      "parentUuid": "ded28e7e_a1df3746",
      "revId": "30e674006d55292500ffff67febac7b08ee9fd75",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "368e4701_23b649e6",
        "filename": "extensions/openpower-pels/src.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 1287,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002351
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-04T14:36:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In this case, the non-redundant systems will have a default chassis number of 0.",
      "parentUuid": "ded28e7e_a1df3746",
      "revId": "30e674006d55292500ffff67febac7b08ee9fd75",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3473d393_581a26c7",
        "filename": "extensions/openpower-pels/src.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 1299,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000008
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T20:32:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this can\u0027t be hardcoded since it may not be true for every system.\nLet me know if you need help thinking of a way to look it up (I\u0027d need to think about it)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1299,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 1299,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "30e674006d55292500ffff67febac7b08ee9fd75",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "74f56e16_0eec420a",
        "filename": "extensions/openpower-pels/src.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 1299,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000427
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-04T02:23:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agree, we should determine the chassis number dynamically instead of deriving it from the BMC position.\n\nMy suggestion is:\n\n* Find all `Item.BMC` object paths using `ObjectMapper.GetSubTreePaths`.\n* If there is only one BMC object:\n\n  * Find its parent `Item.Chassis` object using `ObjectMapper.GetAncestors`.\n  * Get the chassis position from that chassis object.\n* If there are multiple BMC objects:\n\n  * Identify the running BMC using the BMC position.\n  * If the BMC position is valid:\n\n    * Find its parent `Item.Chassis` object using `ObjectMapper.GetAncestors`.\n    * Get the chassis position from that chassis object.\n  * If the BMC position is invalid or unavailable:\n\n    * Follow the existing error-handling flow for the callout section and add debug information to help diagnose the issue.\n\nThis approach should cover:\n\n* Redundant BMC systems\n\n  * Active and passive sides may each have one or more BMC objects.\n* Non-redundant multi-chassis systems\n\n  * A single BMC associated with any chassis.\n* Non-redundant single-chassis systems\n\n  * A single BMC associated with the chassis.\n* Backward compatibility\n\n  * If the chassis position is unavailable and only one BMC object exists, assume chassis 0.\n  \nPlease let me know if any different thoughts or seeing a problem with the above approach.",
      "parentUuid": "3473d393_581a26c7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1299,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 1299,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "30e674006d55292500ffff67febac7b08ee9fd75",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "67c0667e_06ed2e2a",
        "filename": "extensions/openpower-pels/src.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 1299,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000427
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-04T02:27:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note that this involves multiple D-Bus calls. It would be better to cache the chassis position once it has been identified, so that subsequent PEL creations can reuse it instead of determining the running BMC\u0027s chassis position every time.",
      "parentUuid": "74f56e16_0eec420a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1299,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 1299,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "30e674006d55292500ffff67febac7b08ee9fd75",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "34dcf9c8_1f31db82",
        "filename": "extensions/openpower-pels/src.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 1299,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000008
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-04T19:27:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Find its parent Item.Chassis object using ObjectMapper.GetAncestors.\n\nthe trick would be finding the BMC inventory item in the first place, because there will be 2, and the BMC position value doesn\u0027t match the chassis position value.\n\nDid you have a plan for that already?",
      "parentUuid": "67c0667e_06ed2e2a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1299,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 1299,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "30e674006d55292500ffff67febac7b08ee9fd75",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f474a35c_e2691ea6",
        "filename": "extensions/openpower-pels/src.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 1299,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000427
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-05T02:39:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I did not mean that we should use the chassis position to identify the BMC item object.\n\n\u003e Identify the running BMC using the BMC position.\n\nI think there may be some confusion. What I meant is that we should first identify the BMC inventory object using the BMC position, and then use that BMC object path to determine the corresponding chassis object.\n\nFor example:\n\n1. Fetch all `Item.BMC` objects:\n\n```\n/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis2/motherboard/ebmc_card0\n/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis2/motherboard/ebmc_card1\n```\n\n2. Use the running BMC position to select the correct BMC object. The running BMC position is available in:\n\n```\n/run/openbmc/bmc_position\n```\n\nwhich contains either `0` or `1`.\n\nExample:\n\n```\n/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis2/motherboard/ebmc_card0\nPosition: 0\n\n/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis2/motherboard/ebmc_card1\nPosition: 1\n```\n\n3. Once the matching BMC object is identified, use its object path to find the parent chassis object:\n\n```\nGetAncestors(\n    /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis1/motherboard/ebmc_card0,\n    Item.Chassis)\n```\n\nReturns:\n\n```\n/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis1\n```\n\n4. Read the chassis position from the chassis object:\n\n```\n/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis1\nPosition: 1\n```\n\n5. Use this chassis position as the node number/chassis number when calling the VPD APIs.",
      "parentUuid": "34dcf9c8_1f31db82",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1299,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 1299,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "30e674006d55292500ffff67febac7b08ee9fd75",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
